[The 3 additional WPV1 cases confirmed in the above report had been covered on ProMED-mail prior posts, having been reported in the media (see Poliomyelitis update (15): Afghanistan (KD) 20190219.6324856 and Poliomyelitis update (14): Pakistan, Indonesia 20190215.6317666 for the original reports).

The good news is that while it is too early to draw any conclusions, thus far this year (2019) there have not been any cases of cVDPV-associated paralytic polio with dates of onset in 2019 confirmed. Time will tell if this will continue.

