[Reading the above summary of the outbreak of cVDPV1 in Papua New Guinea, I can't help but see the parallels with the early identification of cVDPV1 in Indonesia and the cVDPV2 in Mozambique - identification of the cVDPV in an AFP (acute flaccid paralysis) case and in a contact of that case. So the question remains: Has Indonesia and Mozambique been able to increase active surveillance in the involved provinces and in other provinces in their countries? As said above, only time will tell.

It is promising that the date of onset of paralysis of the most recent case in Papua New Guinea was in late October 2018, almost 4 months ago.

A map showing the provinces in Papua New Guinea can be found at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/papua_map2.htm. - Mod.MPP]

